      <akn:section eId="sec_31_4725">
        <akn:num>31-4725</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Policy language simplification standards.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-4725_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except as provided under ยง 31-4727, no policy forms shall be delivered or issued for delivery in the District of Columbia after the operative date of this section, unless the forms qualify under the following standards;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-4725_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A Flesch reading ease test score shall be measured by the following method:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-4725_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Any other reading test may be approved by the Commissioner as an alternative to the Flesch reading ease test if the alternative is comparable to the Flesch reading ease test.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-4725_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-4725_e">
      <akn:num>(e)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>At the option of the company, riders, endorsements, applications, and other forms made part of the policy form may be scored separately or as part of the policy.</akn:p></akn:content>
